
[1]machiavelian

   MACHIAVE'LIAN, a. [from Machiavel, an Italian writer, secretary and
   historiographer to the republic of Florence.]

   Pertaining to Machiavel, or denoting his principles; politically
   cunning; crafty; cunning in political management.

   MACHIAVE'LIAN, n. One who adopts the principles of Machiavel.
